Text.Value: Vlaakith. Vlaakith! I have wielded your fury as a blade, roared your wrath as a dragon!

EditorData.NodeContext: This is different than usual Lae'zel anger. This is sadness, dejection, betrayal
EditorData.logicalname: Act1b - Vlaakith Betrayal - Laezel was present, Creche not destroyed

Text.Value: And this time, you'd be wise to take me with you.
Your queen is a tyrant, and the situation was a farce. How do you not see that?

EditorData.stateContext: Lae'zel calling to the heavens, to a Vlaakith that cannot hear her.

Text.Value: Fine. Leave me to my thoughts, and I'll leave you to yours.
Remain silent.
You promised ascension - yet I crawl among my own people, low as an asp's belly. Shka'keth!

EditorData.NodeContext: SHKA-keth - asshole. This is different than usual Lae'zel anger. This is sadness, dejection, betrayal
EditorData.logicalname: Followed Vlaakith's orders and was betrayed

Text.Value: She tests me. A trial of faith - K'liir prepared me. 'Only the heaviest souls soar to the Astral.'

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel pauses a moment before speaking. She seeks answers from within.

Text.Value: I followed your path. What good, this heart of stone, for it to be shattered?
I must think.
An impressive show of faith. Will it be enough for our queen?
An impressive show of faith. Will it be enough for your queen?
Yes. Yes. I might gain Vlaakith's favour yet.
Tell Lae'zel what happened in the artefact. Vlaakith's mission was untenable.
Is this to be my penance? Is this heart of stone doomed to shatter?
Now we will be branded Hshar'lak - traitors - because you failed Vlaakith. Our own people will hunt us.
Let's focus on why we're here, and find our cure.
Fine. But I will remind you the zaith'isk has gone unused. If you want your cure, you will return to the crèche.
Yet I crawl among my own people, low as an asp's belly. Shka'keth!

EditorData.NodeContext: SHKA-keth - asshole. This is different than usual Lae'zel anger. This is sadness, dejection, betrayal
EditorData.logicalname: Refused Vlaakith's orders and defeated the inquisitor

Text.Value: I have wielded Vlaakith's fury as a blade, roared her wrath as a dragon - and you have rendered it all for naught.
Your apology means nothing to me.
All this, and you still stand by Vlaakith? You're as dull as you are stupid.
Had I been there, the queen would have known my faith. I would have seen her bidding done!
Tell me what happened inside the artefact. Leave nothing out.
Tell Lae'zel about your encounter with the dream figure.
No, it can't be. All I have given you - my might, my trust - and you left me here to idle for you to deny my venerated queen?
Had I been there, I would have led us to the zaith'isk for purification - and I would have Vlaakith's bidding done!
It would have made every difference.
It would have made no difference. Vlaakith intended for us all to die.
Silence.
Now I will be branded Hshar'lak - traitor - because you failed Vlaakith. My own people will hunt me.
Shka'keth! First I bear the insult of your actions and inactions, and now you mock me with silence?
We're enemies of our own people now. It can't be undone.
You're an enemy of your people now. You need to accept that.
*Your skull buzzes as the events of Crèche Y'llek flow from your mind into Lae'zel's.*

EditorData.NodeContext: This is different than usual Lae'zel anger. This is sadness, dejection, betrayal
EditorData.logicalname: Act1b - Vlaakith Betrayal - Laezel was in Camp, Creche not destroyed

Text.Value: I won't abide another word of this heresy.
Yet I crawl among my own people, low as an asp's belly, slayer of my Queen's inquisitor. Shka'keth!
I'm sorry. I should have taken you with me.

Synopsis: After you recruit the gith, you can click on it to get the following set of questions. The gith will always be semi-hostile at this point. She comes from a hostile land and has been infected by her mortal enemy; she is not here to make friends.
